[Origin: bef. 900; (n.) ME; OE snāw; c. D sneeuw, G Schnee,
ON snǣr, Goth snaiws, L nix (gen. nivis), Gk níps
(acc. nípha), OCS sněgŭ; (v.) ME snowen, deriv. of the n.;
r. ME snewen, OE snīwan; c. OHG snīwan (G schneien), MLG,
MD snīen]

:however she believes (hopes?) it is (exclusively) British.

URLs, references gratefully accepted.
